wednesday in hanoi and phnom penh the cambodian capital 
vietnam previously has said it would withdraw its troops by 
1990 but would move the pullout up to september if a political 
settlement could be reached on the civil war an estimated 70000 
vietnamese troops are in cambodia 
the vietnamese are fighting a coalition of three major 
resistance groups the communist khmer rouge of khieu samphan the 
noncommunist khmer peoples national liberation front of former 
cambodian prime minister son sann and followers of former 
cambodian head of state prince norodom sihanouk 
sihanouk who was deposed in 1970 heads the resistance 
coalition 
vietnam invaded cambodia in december 1978 drove out the radical 
