of government on broadcasters but is only a mild means of 
assuring they provide adequate coverage of important issues 
the bill titled the fairness in broadcasting act of 1989 was 
introduced in january by rep john dingell dmich chairman of 
the full committee cosponsors included markey and a number of 
republicans and is widely expected to pass the house 
dingells committee was expected to take up the bill quickly 
sen daniel inouye dhawaii chairman of the senate commerce 
science and transportation communications subcommittee has 
introduced a companion fairness doctrine bill in the senate 
the federal communications commission repealed its 40yearold 
fairness doctrine in 1987 a federal appeals court in february 
ruled that the fcc had the statutory authority to do so but the 
court did not rule on the issue of the doctrines constitutionality 
if congress writes the doctrine into law a supreme court test 
is likely 
