veto any fairness doctrine bill as president reagan did in june 
1987 after it was passed by congress 
the house passed a fairness doctrine bill again last year but 
it did not come to a vote in the senate 
the fcc in august 1987 struck down two parts of the doctrine 
the first part required broadcasters to provide coverage of 
vitally important controversial issues of interest in the community 
served by the licensees the second said broadcasters must 
provide a reasonable opportunity for the presentation of 
contrasting viewpoints on such issues 
the commission left intact a provision that broadcasters must 
give coverage to ballot issues 
