the number is about 9 percent over the 57 million who were 
granted the extension last year 
the extension is approved for a taxpayer who files a form 4868 
by the midnight april 17 deadline for filing tax returns because 
of the patriots day holiday the deadline is april 18 for residents 
of new england and most areas of new york who file returns to 
andover mass 
however getting an additional four months time to file a 
return does not delay the time for payment of taxes owed form 4868 
must be accompanied by a check for taxes due an underpayment will 
lead to an interest charge and perhaps a penalty 
there was a time when taxpayers could get an automatic twomonth 
extension of filing time simply by arranging to be out of the 
united states or puerto rico on deadline day widespread abuse led 
the irs to end that provision 
now the twomonth delay is available only for taxpayers who 
live and have their business location outside the united states or 
puerto rico and for military personnel outside those areas 
the irs said 581 million returns had been received through 
march 31 compared with 58 million at the same time a year ago the 
irs has processed almost 481 million or 22 percent more than the 
47 million during the period last year 
refunds totaling 305 billion have been certified for 373 
million returns up from the 298 billion and 362 million last 
year the average refund this year is 819 down from 825 a year 
ago 
about 109 million returns are expected to be filed this year 
