a centuryold clock in this 
quintessential new england town has pitted oldtimers fond of its 
hourly chiming against a pair of newcomers who say the clamor is 
taking a toll on their sleep 
the couple sued to silence the town clock at night and that is 
the talk of the main street barbershop just a stones throw from 
the first congregational church steeple that holds the clock said 
barber giles desmond 
any time anything happens that might undermine the towns 
history people get very how shall i say hostile said 
