<TEXT>
key events in cambodia beginning with 
the coup in 1970 
march 18 1970 a coup by gen lon nol ousts prince norodom 
sihanouk who had ruled since 1941 and cambodia becomes a major 
front of the vietnam war 
april 17 1975 the communist khmer rouge led by pol pot gain 
power and try to create a primitive agrarian society killing 
hundreds of thousands of people in slave labor camps and execution 
chambers 
dec 25 1978 vietnam invades cambodia to stop khmer rouge 
border attacks that began in 1977 khmer rouge forces are driven to 
the thai border area 
jan 10 1979 vietnam installs the government of president 
heng samrin in phnom penh 
feb 1979 china conducts a border war against vietnam to 
punish it for the invasion 
june 22 1982 the khmer rouge and guerrilla groups led by 
sihanouk and former premier son sann form a resistance coalition 
aug 16 1985 vietnam announces it will withdraw all its 
troops by 1990 with or without a political settlement 
july 29 1987 indonesia representing the association of 
southeast asian nations and vietnam sign an agreement calling for 
talks among all the warring parties 
july 29 1987 sihanouk holds unprecedented peace talks in 
france with premier hun sen of the vietnamsponsored government in 
phnom penh 
may 26 1988 vietnam says it will withdraw 50000 soldiers 
described as half its force in cambodia by the end of the year 
june 30 1988 officials say vietnams high command is 
withdrawn from cambodia and the running of the civil war turned 
over to phnom penh 
july 2528 1988 vietnam meets the cambodian resistance for 
the first time in peace talks at bogor indonesia a consensus 
emerges that vietnamese withdrawal must be linked to preventing a 
return to power by the khmer rouge 
nov 68 1988 sihanouk and hun sen hold their third meeting 
this time joined by son sann 
dec 19 1988 chinas premier li peng says china will decrease 
aid to the resistance as vietnam withdraws and halt aid when the 
troops are gone 
feb 14 1989 foreign minister eduard shevardnadze makes the 
highestlevel soviet visit to china in 30 years and broad agreement 
is reached on cambodia may 1518 for the first summit since the 
1950s 
feb 9 1989 the latest resistance peace plan calls for a 
2000member un force to supervise vietnams withdrawal and 
prevent a khmer rouge return a fourparty coalition government and 
a limit of 10000 fighters in each faction 
feb 1618 1989 disagreement arises at preparatory meetings 
for a second round of peace talks 
feb 1921 1989 the second session of talks in jakarta 
indonesia ends with no progress and divergences of views 
participants say the resistance accuses vietnam and its cambodian 
ally of blocking peace 
wednesday vietnam announces it will withdraw all forces by 
sept 30 
