william bryan cruse jr 61 stood with bowed head and crossed 
arms as circuit judge john antoon read off the 32 guilty verdicts 
there was no reaction or comment from the frail bearded defendant 
the jury deliberated 10 hours over two days before finding 
cruse guilty of six counts of firstdegree murder 22 counts of 
attempted firstdegree murder two counts of attempted 
seconddegree murder one count of kidnapping and one count of 
false imprisonment 
were happy that the jury rejected the insanity defense and 
found it was an act of coldblooded murder said state attorney 
norm wolfinger 
the sentencing phase of the trial in which jurors recommend a 
nonbinding verdict of death or a life sentence begins april 17 
just a week before the second anniversary of the rampage at two 
palm bay shopping centers 
it would be up to cruse to decide whether to appeal said public 
defender jr russo whose office represented the defendant 
ive said all along i wanted him found guilty that i wanted 
him executed and that i wanted to pull the switch said vi 
johnson mother of gerald johnson one of two police officers among 
the six people killed 
her 27yearold son lay wounded on the pavement next to his 
patrol car in the winndixie supermarket parking lot when cruse 
approached with his highpowered rifle and fired three more bullets 
into him 
the prosecution argued this was only one example rebutting 
defense contentions that the gunman was insane and didnt know what 
he was doing 
the defense argued that cruse had been mentally ill for years 
and was acting under delusions that everyone considered him 
homosexual psychiatrists on both sides of the issue agreed on his 
mental illness but disagreed sharply on the issue of legal insanity 
under florida law 
in addition to mental illness this requires a finding that the 
defendant not know what he was doing or the consequences and that 
he did not know it was wrong 
the shootout started when cruse drove up to the publix store 
after an afternoon of drinking beer he began firing from his car 
and almost immediately killed nobil alhameli 25 and altawakuly 
18 kuwaitis attending a local college as they emerged from a 
store 
cruse then drove across the street into sabal palm square got 
out of his car shot johnson and officer ronald grogan 28 and 
fired dozens of other shots as motorists and pedestrians fled and 
sought cover 
he killed 67yearold ruth green as she sat in her car he shot 
out the front windows of the winndixie store stormed in 
sporadically firing his semiautomatic ruger mini14 and sending 
dozens of shoppers fleeing out the back the sixth victim lester 
watson 51 was killed at that time 
cruse then found two store employees hiding in a restroom and 
forced them out he released one but held the other hostage for 
about seven hours at about 2 am he released her and police 
fired tear gas to force him out 
cruse has a history of mental instability and bizarre actions 
daing to the 1970s in his hometown of lexington ky according to 
psychiatrists and defense witnesses he came to florida in 1985 
his main trial lawyer marlene alva called cruse a madman a 
crazy person someone who went berserk 
