south africa called wednesday for black 
nationalist guerrillas to surrender or face more attacks in the 
5dayold battle that has left at least 200 people dead 
the leader of the southwest africa peoples organization said 
his guerrilla fighters had no intention of leaving the south 
africancontrolled territory a newspaper reported 
