<TEXT>
a scathing portrait of the late cary grant has 
hit bookstores under the title the lonely heart 
the books name is taken from one of the actors 72 feature 
films none but the lonely heart but another grant movie might 
provide a more appropriate title the awful truth 
written by charles higham author of biographies on marlon 
brando and katharine hepburn and roy moseley who has written 
about merle oberon and rex harrison the lonely heart talks 
about the stars numerous homosexual affairs stormy marraiges and 
battles on film sets with directors and fellow actors 
the book alleges that grant whose real name was archibald 
leach was born out of wedlock to a jewish woman secretly acted as 
an agent for several hollywood stars and worked for british 
intelligence during world war ii the lonely heart also repeats 
the story of his admitted use of lsd 
even the books index provides unflattering coverage a quick 
check under grant cary lists headings for the following as 
liar his nose stinginess showing his age and 
faked suicide attempt under the heading homosexuality the 
book urges readers to see also bisexuality of 
grant whose movies include his girl friday to catch a 
thief north by northwest and gunga din died in 1986 at 
the age of 82 
despite the trashing grant receives the authors do praise his 
acting skills and present many fond reminiscences from old friends 
cary grant despite his many very human failings did his best to 
be a good and decent man the authors conclude in a preface 
it really is not a muckraking book higham said in an 
interview nor is it a fan book i try to balance everything i 
see my biographies of stars as a continuing social history told 
through biography i suppose people will look back on this age and 
say what were they like who were these people 
moseley and higham draw on interviews with several dozen people 
for the lonely heart including hepburn who costarred with 
grant in four films marlene dietrich and virginia cherrill the 
actors first wife 
grants life is shown beginning with his birth in bristol 
england in 1904 up to the very last hours before his fatal stroke 
higham who met grant on several occasions says he was 
fascinated by the differences between the stars public and private 
behavior i had been raised where people who were gracious and 
polite really were gracious and polite they didnt have two 
personalities the londonborn author said i think the 
contrast between the violence and tension in private and the utter 
charm with a reporter that made me realize many celebrities had 
enormous conflicts even schizophrenia 
grants conflicts seem to have begun at birth his father elias 
leach was a suit presser who had several girlfriends the lonely 
heart reports that although both elias leach and his wife elsie 
were gentiles they had the infant circumcised a traditional 
jewish custom grant would later make generous donations to israel 
in honor of his dead jewish mother 
the young archibald leach quickly displayed exceptional athletic 
ability and was just in his midteens when he joined the pender 
troupe a traveling company of acrobats in the early 1930s leach 
headed for hollywood where he had a contract with paramount 
pictures and quickly was renamed cary grant the first name 
derived from cary lockwood a character he played in a stage show 
the last name was chosen by studio publicists 
rumors of grants homosexual relationships surfaced quickly 
higham recalled a conversation he had in the 60s with dietrich 
who starred in blonde venus one of grants first films 
one night we were at dinner and i asked her about blonde 
venus and whether she had had any offscreen relationship with 
cary grant she responded oh no that was out of the question 
becuase he was homosexual it was simply a given it was 
understood to be the case 
in 1932 grant met cherrill an actress who portrayed the blind 
girl in charlie chaplins classic city lights and married her 
in 1934 by all accounts they were an unhappy couple with grant 
given to furious temper tantrums and even physical violence they 
were divorced the following year grant would marry four more 
times and had one child jennifer with the actress dyan cannon 
his fourth wife 
by 1937 grants work in topper and the awful truth had 
made him one of hollywoods most popular leading men his good 
looks lilting english accent and quick wit were the perfect 
ingredients for light romantic comedies grant would go on to 
appear opposite some of the worlds most beautiful actresses 
including grace kelly ingrid bergman and sophia loren he was 
still a major boxoffice draw when he retired in 1966 
but while his screen image was carefree and charming higham and 
moseley write that he was privately tormented by conflicting sexual 
desires and insecurity over his success 
on the screen there is no one more relaxed more dapper 
seeminginly more cool higham said yet this was achieved at 
considerably more cost it interests me that some people would 
rather not know this 
according to higham and moseley grant secretly went into 
business in the mid30s with an old friend frank vincent along 
with film agent harry edington they operated a firm whose 
clientele included dietrich and rita hayworth 
i think one of the most surprising things was that he was a 
hollywood agent higham said he was picking up a percentage of 
a percentage frank vincent had become a very powerful agent he 
was running around getting people deals 
higham said curiosity was his main reason for doing the book 
i got to know him on a very superficial social level the 
author said i found him very interesting but very aloof i hoped 
the book would be a solution to a mystery i saw him as a puzzling 
mystery around whom many others flew 
</TEXT>
