<TEXT>
petroleum prices plunged wednesday as traders 
reacted to a range of negative news by unloading energy futures 
driving down the price of unleaded gasoline by more than 3 cents a 
gallon 
trading was brisk on the new york mercantile exchange during a 
selloff that wiped away most of the gains achieved in the previous 
session 
the may contract for west texas intermediate the benchmark 
grade of us crude settled 43 cents lower at 1999 a barrel the 
contract had gone up 47 cents a barrel on tuesday 
among refined petroleum products traded on the exchange the may 
contract for unleaded gasoline slid by 303 cents to 6643 cents a 
gallon the contract had risen by 161 cents and 088 cent on 
tuesday and monday respectively 
may wholesale home heating oil which rose 089 cent tuesday 
fell 201 cents to 5163 cents a gallon 
jerry samuels an energy broker at shearson lehman hutton inc 
said the selling came in response to reports stating that opec 
lately has exceeded its crude production quota and that traffic and 
output in alaska have returned to normal following the disruptions 
caused by one of the worlds worst oil spills 
it was a wild day several bearish elements sent the market 
down samuels said 
the price retreat occurred despite an industry report showing an 
uncommonly large drop in crude oil stocks during the latest week 
the american petroleum institute said for the week ended march 31 
domestic crude oil stocks fell 128 million barrels to 32458 
million 
crude inventories have been drawn down due to delays in 
shipments from alaskas oil fields while a cleanup operation takes 
place 
it was reported wednesday that flow through the alaskan pipeline 
returned to its normal daily level of 21 million barrels 
oil flow from the north slope had been cut by 60 percent because 
the spill restricted tanker traffic in valdez harbor but traffic 
has increased 
energy prices have rallied recently responding to the temporary 
supply squeeze in the aftermath of a massive oil spill by an exxon 
corp tanker at the valdez alaska port 
there was no confirmation of reports concerning the organization 
of petroleum exporting countries crude oil output levels 
</TEXT>
