<TEXT>
the dollar moved moderately higher wednesday 
against major foreign currencies in what analysts called a 
technical adjustment following its recent slump 
gold prices fell republic national bank of new york quoted a 
bid of 38330 for a troy ounce of gold as of 4 pm edt down from 
38590 late tuesday 
wednesdays modest gains at least temporarily ended the dollars 
decline which began last week at that time the central banks of 
several nations intervened in the foreign exchange markets to bring 
the us currency lower 
but ronald holzer chief foreign exchange dealer with harris 
trust amp savings bank in chicago said the dollars advance 
wednesday was a minor adjustment and that the currencys outlook 
remained bearish partly because the seven major industrial nations 
have restated their desire for stable interest rates 
