<TEXT>
david i shapiro who was appointed bankruptcy 
examiner wednesday for strikebound eastern airlines is a 
washington attorney who has practiced civil liberties and antitrust 
law 
us bankruptcy judge burton lifland has ruled that the examiner 
in the eastern case should have unusually broad powers including a 
mandate to mediate the bitter labor dispute at the airline and get 
its planes flying again 
shapiro 60 is a senior partner of dickstein shapiro amp morin 
a law firm based in washington his clients have included american 
telephone amp telegraph co u s west first national bank of 
chicago labor unions and professional associations 
he also served as the settlement master in the agent orange 
chemical liability trial in which vietnam veterans successfully 
sued seven makers of the defoliant the veterans claimed agent 
orange which was used to kill vegetation in vietnam caused 
cancer birth defects and other disabilities 
a native of brooklyn ny shapiro practiced mainly civil 
liberties law in the 1950s and early 1960s and successfully argued 
three such cases before the us supreme court in more recent 
years he has devoted his practice to major antitrust cases in 
which he represented about 20 states and other government entities 
he is a graduate of the university of wisconsin brooklyn 
college and brooklyn law school 
</TEXT>
